Styling Functions:

We need to keep a few details in mind when you're styling functions.
Functions should have  descriptive names and these name should use
lowercase letters and underscores. Descriptive names help you
and other understand what your code is trying to do. Module name should 
use these conventions as well.

Every function should have have a comment that explains concisely what
the function does. This comment shoulf appear immediately after the function
definition and use the docstring format. In a well-documented function, other programers can use the 
function by reading the description in the docstring. They should be able to use it in the programs.

If you specify a defaulf value for a parameter, no spaces should be used on either side of the equal sign

def function_name(parameter_0, parameter_1="defaulf_value")

The same convention should be used for keyword arguments in function calls

function_name(value_0, parameter_1="default_value")
